CHINA, 1989: THE SHATTERED DREAM 
Beijing's bloody suppression of student protesters June 3-4 and harsh crackdown 
on dissent sent a shock wave of revulsion around the world. 
In Sunday's editions of The Times, a special 12-page report, "The Shattered 
Dream, China/1989," examines the roots of the dramatic events, the crackdown 
and prospects for the future, including vivid details and new photos of the 
massacre. 
